4 §1281. Standard automobile insurance form
5 The commissioner of insurance may promulgate such any rules and
6 regulations as necessary to establish reasonable standard provisions to be included
7 in all policies of automobile insurance delivered or issued for delivery in this state.
8 All such policies shall be written in language that can be easily understood by most
9 automobile insurance consumers.
10 §1282. Standard motor vehicle insurance form; prohibited provisions
11 No A motor vehicle liability insurance policy nor any or uninsured motorist
12 coverage for bodily injury shall not limit the coverage of, or the amount that can be
13 recovered by, the named insured, or the spouse or other family member of the named
14 insured, or express or implied permissive users, for whom the policy provides
15 coverage, to any amount less than the highest policy limit provided in the policy for
16 the respective coverage or potential recovery. Any recovery is limited to damages
17 actually sustained. Any provision of a motor vehicle insurance policy issued in, or
18 for delivery in, the state of Louisiana that is not in accord with this Section is
19 contrary to the public policy of this state and shall be null, void, and unenforceable.
